{
  "video_id": "96HHmILhyrE",
  "title": "Glow-in-the-dark sharks and other stunning sea creatures | David Gruber",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 12738.0,
      "end_time": 15898.0,
      "text": "I&#39;m a marine biologist and an explorer-photographer"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 15922.0,
      "end_time": 17663.0,
      "text": "with National Geographic,"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 17687.0,
      "end_time": 19365.0,
      "text": "but I want to share a secret."
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 19793.0,
      "end_time": 23436.0,
      "text": "This image is totally incorrect,"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 23460.0,
      "end_time": 25197.0,
      "text": "totally incorrect."
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 25221.0,
      "end_time": 27348.0,
      "text": "I see a couple of people crying in the back"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 27372.0,
      "end_time": 29816.0,
      "text": "that I&#39;ve blown their idea of mermaids."
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 29840.0,
      "end_time": 32491.0,
      "text": "All right, the mermaid is indeed real,"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 32515.0,
      "end_time": 34650.0,
      "text": "but anyone who&#39;s gone on a dive"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 34674.0,
      "end_time": 37272.0,
      "text": "will know that the ocean looks more like this."
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 37767.0,
      "end_time": 41267.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s because the ocean is this massive filter,"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 41291.0,
      "end_time": 43364.0,
      "text": "and as soon as you start going underwater,"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 43388.0,
      "end_time": 45610.0,
      "text": "you&#39;re going to lose your colors,"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 45850.0,
      "end_time": 48291.0,
      "text": "and it&#39;s going to get dark and blue very quickly."
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 48315.0,
      "end_time": 51990.0,
      "text": "But we&#39;re humans -- we&#39;re terrestrial mammals."
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 51124.0,
      "end_time": 53299.0,
      "text": "And we&#39;ve got trichromatic vision,"
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 53323.0,
      "end_time": 55989.0,
      "text": "so we see in red, green and blue,"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 56130.0,
      "end_time": 58338.0,
      "text": "and we&#39;re just complete color addicts."
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 58362.0,
      "end_time": 61500.0,
      "text": "We love eye-popping color,"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 61290.0,
      "end_time": 63616.0,
      "text": "and we try to bring this eye-popping color"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 63640.0,
      "end_time": 65190.0,
      "text": "underwater with us."
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 65440.0,
      "end_time": 69810.0,
      "text": "So there&#39;s been a long and sordid history of bringing color underwater,"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 69105.0,
      "end_time": 74510.0,
      "text": "and it starts 88 years ago with Bill Longley and Charles Martin,"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 74750.0,
      "end_time": 76996.0,
      "text": "who were trying to take the first underwater color photograph."
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 77200.0,
      "end_time": 79735.0,
      "text": "And they&#39;re in there with old-school scuba suits,"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 79759.0,
      "end_time": 81884.0,
      "text": "where you&#39;re pumping air down to them,"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 81908.0,
      "end_time": 87498.0,
      "text": "and they&#39;ve got a pontoon of high-explosive magnesium powder,"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 87522.0,
      "end_time": 89729.0,
      "text": "and the poor people at the surface are not sure"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 89753.0,
      "end_time": 93383.0,
      "text": "when they&#39;re going to pull the string when they&#39;ve got their frame in focus,"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 93407.0,
      "end_time": 96331.0,
      "text": "and -- boom! -- a pound of high explosives would go off"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 96355.0,
      "end_time": 99410.0,
      "text": "so they could put a little bit of light underwater"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 99434.0,
      "end_time": 102204.0,
      "text": "and get an image like this beautiful hogfish."
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 102228.0,
      "end_time": 105770.0,
      "text": "I mean, it&#39;s a gorgeous image, but this is not real."
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 105101.0,
      "end_time": 107860.0,
      "text": "They&#39;re creating an artificial environment"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 107884.0,
      "end_time": 111560.0,
      "text": "so we can satisfy our own addiction to color."
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 111996.0,
      "end_time": 115824.0,
      "text": "And looking at it the other way, what we&#39;ve been finding"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 115848.0,
      "end_time": 119510.0,
      "text": "is that instead of bringing color underwater with us,"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 119760.0,
      "end_time": 121827.0,
      "text": "that we&#39;ve been looking at the blue ocean,"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 121852.0,
      "end_time": 124114.0,
      "text": "and it&#39;s a crucible of blue,"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 124138.0,
      "end_time": 127234.0,
      "text": "and these animals living there for millions of years"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 127258.0,
      "end_time": 131787.0,
      "text": "have been evolving all sorts of ways to take in that blue light"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 131812.0,
      "end_time": 133503.0,
      "text": "and give off other colors."
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 133527.0,
      "end_time": 136813.0,
      "text": "And here&#39;s just a little sample of what this secret world looks like."
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 136837.0,
      "end_time": 138714.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s like an underwater light show."
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 138739.0,
      "end_time": 142823.0,
      "text": "(Music)"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 143495.0,
      "end_time": 147415.0,
      "text": "Again, what we&#39;re seeing here is blue light hitting this image."
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 147439.0,
      "end_time": 149528.0,
      "text": "These animals are absorbing the blue light"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 149552.0,
      "end_time": 152330.0,
      "text": "and immediately transforming this light."
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 155390.0,
      "end_time": 159762.0,
      "text": "So if you think about it, the ocean is 71 percent of the planet,"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 159787.0,
      "end_time": 163857.0,
      "text": "and blue light can extend down to almost a 1,000 meters."
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 163881.0,
      "end_time": 165985.0,
      "text": "As we go down underwater,"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 166900.0,
      "end_time": 168702.0,
      "text": "after about 10 meters, all the red is gone."
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 168727.0,
      "end_time": 171930.0,
      "text": "So if you see anything under 10 meters that&#39;s red,"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 171954.0,
      "end_time": 175120.0,
      "text": "it&#39;s an animal transforming and creating its own red."
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 175472.0,
      "end_time": 181725.0,
      "text": "This is the largest single monochromatic blue environment on our planet."
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 182670.0,
      "end_time": 187359.0,
      "text": "And my gateway into this world of biofluorescence begins with corals."
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 187384.0,
      "end_time": 189470.0,
      "text": "And I want to give a full TED Talk on corals"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 189494.0,
      "end_time": 191296.0,
      "text": "and just how cool these things are."
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 191320.0,
      "end_time": 194542.0,
      "text": "One of the things that they do, one of their miraculous feats,"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 194566.0,
      "end_time": 197344.0,
      "text": "is they produce lots of these fluorescent proteins,"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 197368.0,
      "end_time": 198853.0,
      "text": "fluorescent molecules."
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 198877.0,
      "end_time": 203624.0,
      "text": "And in this coral, it could be making up to 14 percent of its body mass --"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 203648.0,
      "end_time": 205733.0,
      "text": "could be this fluorescent protein."
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 205757.0,
      "end_time": 210186.0,
      "text": "So you wouldn&#39;t be making, like, 14 percent muscle and not using it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 210210.0,
      "end_time": 213794.0,
      "text": "so it&#39;s likely doing something that has a functional role."
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 213818.0,
      "end_time": 217655.0,
      "text": "And for the last 10, 15 years, this was so special to me,"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 217679.0,
      "end_time": 223990.0,
      "text": "because this molecule has turned out to be one of the most revolutionary tools"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 223123.0,
      "end_time": 224822.0,
      "text": "in biomedical science,"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 224847.0,
      "end_time": 228361.0,
      "text": "and it&#39;s allowing us to better see inside ourselves."
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 229464.0,
      "end_time": 231805.0,
      "text": "So, how do I study this?"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 231829.0,
      "end_time": 234900.0,
      "text": "In order to study biofluorescence, we swim at night."
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 234924.0,
      "end_time": 236302.0,
      "text": "And when I started out,"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 236326.0,
      "end_time": 240337.0,
      "text": "I was just using these blue duct-tape filters over my strobe,"
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 240361.0,
      "end_time": 242739.0,
      "text": "so I could make sure I&#39;m actually seeing the light"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 242764.0,
      "end_time": 244796.0,
      "text": "that&#39;s being transformed by the animals."
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 244820.0,
      "end_time": 248297.0,
      "text": "We&#39;re making an exhibit for the Museum of Natural History,"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 248321.0,
      "end_time": 252128.0,
      "text": "and we&#39;re trying to show off how great the fluorescent corals are on the reef,"
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 252152.0,
      "end_time": 255208.0,
      "text": "and something happened that just blew me away:"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 255232.0,
      "end_time": 256620.0,
      "text": "this."
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 256644.0,
      "end_time": 258460.0,
      "text": "In the middle of our corals,"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 258485.0,
      "end_time": 261491.0,
      "text": "is this green fluorescent fish."
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 261515.0,
      "end_time": 264327.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s the first time we&#39;ve ever seen a green fluorescent fish"
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 264351.0,
      "end_time": 265978.0,
      "text": "or any vertebrate for that matter."
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 266200.0,
      "end_time": 268557.0,
      "text": "And we&#39;re rubbing our eyes, checking the filters,"
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 268581.0,
      "end_time": 271780.0,
      "text": "thinking that somebody&#39;s maybe playing a joke on us with the camera,"
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 271804.0,
      "end_time": 273746.0,
      "text": "but the eel was real."
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 273771.0,
      "end_time": 277310.0,
      "text": "It was the first green fluorescent eel that we found,"
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 277334.0,
      "end_time": 280293.0,
      "text": "and this just changed my trajectory completely."
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 280317.0,
      "end_time": 283651.0,
      "text": "So I had to put down my corals and team up"
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 283675.0,
      "end_time": 285708.0,
      "text": "with a fish scientist, John Sparks,"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 285732.0,
      "end_time": 288231.0,
      "text": "and begin a search around the world"
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 288255.0,
      "end_time": 291506.0,
      "text": "to see how prevalent this phenomenon is."
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 291530.0,
      "end_time": 294500.0,
      "text": "And fish are much more interesting than corals,"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 294290.0,
      "end_time": 296243.0,
      "text": "because they have really advanced vision,"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 296267.0,
      "end_time": 300520.0,
      "text": "and some of the fish even have, the way that I was photographing it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 300760.0,
      "end_time": 303512.0,
      "text": "they have lenses in their eyes that would magnify the fluorescence."
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 303536.0,
      "end_time": 305846.0,
      "text": "So I wanted to seek this out further."
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 305870.0,
      "end_time": 307592.0,
      "text": "So we designed a new set of gear"
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 307616.0,
      "end_time": 309905.0,
      "text": "and we&#39;re scouring the reefs around the world,"
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 309929.0,
      "end_time": 311508.0,
      "text": "looking for fluorescent life."
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 311532.0,
      "end_time": 313587.0,
      "text": "And it&#39;s a bit like \"E.T. phone home.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 313611.0,
      "end_time": 316320.0,
      "text": "We&#39;re out there swimming with this blue light,"
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 316344.0,
      "end_time": 318549.0,
      "text": "and we&#39;re looking for a response,"
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 318573.0,
      "end_time": 322147.0,
      "text": "for animals to be absorbing the light and transferring this back to us."
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 322172.0,
      "end_time": 326884.0,
      "text": "And eventually, we found our photobombing Kaupichphys eel."
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 326908.0,
      "end_time": 331378.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s a really shy, reclusive eel that we know almost nothing about."
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 331402.0,
      "end_time": 333363.0,
      "text": "They&#39;re only about the size of my finger,"
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 333387.0,
      "end_time": 337867.0,
      "text": "and they spend about 99.9 percent of their time hidden under a rock."
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 337891.0,
      "end_time": 342120.0,
      "text": "But these eels do come out to mate under full-moon nights,"
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 342360.0,
      "end_time": 345529.0,
      "text": "and that full-moon night translates underwater to blue."
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 345553.0,
      "end_time": 348820.0,
      "text": "Perhaps they&#39;re using this as a way to see each other,"
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 348107.0,
      "end_time": 349568.0,
      "text": "quickly find each other, mate,"
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 349592.0,
      "end_time": 353306.0,
      "text": "go back into their hole for the next long stint of time."
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 353330.0,
      "end_time": 356210.0,
      "text": "But then we started to find other fluorescent marine life,"
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 356234.0,
      "end_time": 359310.0,
      "text": "like this green fluorescent bream,"
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 359550.0,
      "end_time": 363400.0,
      "text": "with its, like, racing stripes along its head and its nape,"
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 363640.0,
      "end_time": 367365.0,
      "text": "and it&#39;s almost camouflaged and fluorescing at the same intensity"
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 367389.0,
      "end_time": 369175.0,
      "text": "as the fluorescent coral there."
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 370190.0,
      "end_time": 372277.0,
      "text": "After this fish,"
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 372301.0,
      "end_time": 376602.0,
      "text": "we were introduced to this red fluorescent scorpionfish"
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 376626.0,
      "end_time": 378768.0,
      "text": "cloaked and hidden on this rock."
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 378793.0,
      "end_time": 382594.0,
      "text": "The only time we&#39;ve ever seen this, it&#39;s either on red fluorescent algae"
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 382618.0,
      "end_time": 384293.0,
      "text": "or red fluorescent coral."
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 384634.0,
      "end_time": 389967.0,
      "text": "Later, we found this stealthy green fluorescent lizardfish."
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 389991.0,
      "end_time": 392790.0,
      "text": "These lizardfish come in many varieties,"
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 392103.0,
      "end_time": 395372.0,
      "text": "and they look almost exactly alike under white light."
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 395396.0,
      "end_time": 397770.0,
      "text": "But if you look at them under fluorescent light,"
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 397794.0,
      "end_time": 399195.0,
      "text": "you see lots of patterns,"
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 399219.0,
      "end_time": 401905.0,
      "text": "you can really see the differences among them."
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 401929.0,
      "end_time": 404866.0,
      "text": "And in total -- we just reported this last year --"
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 404890.0,
      "end_time": 409238.0,
      "text": "we found over 200 species of biofluorescent fish."
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 410135.0,
      "end_time": 416610.0,
      "text": "One of my inspirations is French artist and biologist Jean Painlevé."
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 416850.0,
      "end_time": 420133.0,
      "text": "He really captures this entrepreneuring, creative spirit in biology."
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 420158.0,
      "end_time": 423961.0,
      "text": "He would design his own gear, make his own cameras,"
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 423985.0,
      "end_time": 427979.0,
      "text": "and he was fascinated with the seahorse, Hippocampus erectus,"
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 428300.0,
      "end_time": 431229.0,
      "text": "and he filmed for the first time the seahorse giving birth."
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 432860.0,
      "end_time": 433638.0,
      "text": "So this is the male seahorse."
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 433662.0,
      "end_time": 438376.0,
      "text": "They were one of the first fish to start swimming upright"
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 438400.0,
      "end_time": 440270.0,
      "text": "with their brain above their head."
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 440520.0,
      "end_time": 441203.0,
      "text": "The males give birth,"
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 441227.0,
      "end_time": 442647.0,
      "text": "just phenomenal creatures."
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 444955.0,
      "end_time": 446296.0,
      "text": "So he stayed awake for days."
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 446321.0,
      "end_time": 449496.0,
      "text": "He even put this electrical visor on his head that would shock him,"
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 449520.0,
      "end_time": 451111.0,
      "text": "so he could capture this moment."
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 452796.0,
      "end_time": 454916.0,
      "text": "Now, I wish I could have shown Painlevé"
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 454940.0,
      "end_time": 458370.0,
      "text": "the moment where we found biofluorescent seahorses"
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 458610.0,
      "end_time": 460760.0,
      "text": "in the exact same species that he was studying."
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 460784.0,
      "end_time": 461998.0,
      "text": "And here&#39;s our footage."
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 462220.0,
      "end_time": 464849.0,
      "text": "(Music)"
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 466476.0,
      "end_time": 467943.0,
      "text": "They&#39;re the most cryptic fish."
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 467967.0,
      "end_time": 471347.0,
      "text": "You could be swimming right on top of them and not see the seahorse."
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 472228.0,
      "end_time": 476736.0,
      "text": "They would blend right into the algae, which would also fluoresce red,"
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 476760.0,
      "end_time": 478221.0,
      "text": "but they&#39;ve got great vision,"
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 478245.0,
      "end_time": 480419.0,
      "text": "and they go through this long mating ritual,"
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 480443.0,
      "end_time": 482544.0,
      "text": "and perhaps they&#39;re using it in that effect."
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 483647.0,
      "end_time": 486566.0,
      "text": "But things got pretty edgy"
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 487442.0,
      "end_time": 492455.0,
      "text": "when we found green fluorescence in the stingray,"
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 492479.0,
      "end_time": 495243.0,
      "text": "because stingrays are in the Elasmobranch class,"
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 495267.0,
      "end_time": 496506.0,
      "text": "which includes ..."
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 497750.0,
      "end_time": 498534.0,
      "text": "sharks."
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 498558.0,
      "end_time": 501756.0,
      "text": "So I&#39;m, like, a coral biologist."
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 502161.0,
      "end_time": 505606.0,
      "text": "Somebody&#39;s got to go down and check to see if the sharks are fluorescent."
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 505630.0,
      "end_time": 506892.0,
      "text": "And there I am."
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 506916.0,
      "end_time": 508314.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 508338.0,
      "end_time": 510877.0,
      "text": "And I was like, \"Maybe I should go back to corals.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 510901.0,
      "end_time": 511933.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 511957.0,
      "end_time": 514352.0,
      "text": "It turns out that these sharks are not fluorescent."
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 515472.0,
      "end_time": 516889.0,
      "text": "And then we found it."
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 516913.0,
      "end_time": 521751.0,
      "text": "In a deep, dark canyon off the coast of California,"
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 521775.0,
      "end_time": 526212.0,
      "text": "we found the first biofluorescent swellshark,"
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 526236.0,
      "end_time": 528110.0,
      "text": "right underneath all the surfers."
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 528350.0,
      "end_time": 529219.0,
      "text": "Here it is."
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 529244.0,
      "end_time": 531968.0,
      "text": "They&#39;re just about a meter long. It&#39;s called a swellshark."
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 531992.0,
      "end_time": 534904.0,
      "text": "And they call them a swellshark because if they&#39;re threatened,"
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 534928.0,
      "end_time": 537674.0,
      "text": "they can gulp down water and blow up like an inner tube,"
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 537698.0,
      "end_time": 538857.0,
      "text": "about twice their size,"
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 538881.0,
      "end_time": 543626.0,
      "text": "and wedge themselves under a rock, so they don&#39;t get eaten by a predator."
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 544158.0,
      "end_time": 548301.0,
      "text": "And here is our first footage of these biofluorescent swellsharks."
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 549229.0,
      "end_time": 553950.0,
      "text": "Just magnificent -- I mean, they&#39;re showing these distinct patterns,"
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 553974.0,
      "end_time": 557547.0,
      "text": "and there are areas that are fluorescent and areas that are not fluorescent,"
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 557571.0,
      "end_time": 560160.0,
      "text": "but they&#39;ve also got these twinkling spots on them"
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 560184.0,
      "end_time": 562775.0,
      "text": "that are much brighter than other parts of the shark."
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 562799.0,
      "end_time": 565326.0,
      "text": "But this is all beautiful to see."
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 565350.0,
      "end_time": 566980.0,
      "text": "I was like, this is gorgeous."
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 567400.0,
      "end_time": 569835.0,
      "text": "But what does it mean to the shark?"
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 569859.0,
      "end_time": 571206.0,
      "text": "Can they see this?"
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 571230.0,
      "end_time": 572762.0,
      "text": "And we looked in the literature,"
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 572786.0,
      "end_time": 575944.0,
      "text": "and nothing was known about this shark&#39;s vision."
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 575968.0,
      "end_time": 580150.0,
      "text": "So I took this shark to eye specialist Ellis Loew at Cornell University,"
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 580174.0,
      "end_time": 583697.0,
      "text": "and we found out that this shark sees discretely and acutely"
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 583721.0,
      "end_time": 585815.0,
      "text": "in the blue-green interface,"
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 585839.0,
      "end_time": 588669.0,
      "text": "probably about 100 times better than we can see in the dark,"
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 588693.0,
      "end_time": 590419.0,
      "text": "but they only see blue-green."
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 590443.0,
      "end_time": 593562.0,
      "text": "So what it&#39;s doing is taking this blue world"
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 593586.0,
      "end_time": 596339.0,
      "text": "and it&#39;s absorbing the blue, creating green."
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 596363.0,
      "end_time": 599181.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s creating contrast that they can indeed see."
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 599205.0,
      "end_time": 600356.0,
      "text": "So we have a model,"
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 600380.0,
      "end_time": 603752.0,
      "text": "showing that it creates an ability for them to see all these patterns."
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 603776.0,
      "end_time": 606656.0,
      "text": "And males and females also have, we&#39;re finding,"
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 606681.0,
      "end_time": 608617.0,
      "text": "distinct patterns among them."
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 609276.0,
      "end_time": 614709.0,
      "text": "But our last find came really just a few miles from where we are now,"
    },
    {
      "index": 202,
      "start_time": 614733.0,
      "end_time": 616184.0,
      "text": "in the Solomon Islands."
    },
    {
      "index": 203,
      "start_time": 616208.0,
      "end_time": 620668.0,
      "text": "Swimming at night, I encountered the first biofluorescent sea turtle."
    },
    {
      "index": 204,
      "start_time": 620692.0,
      "end_time": 624104.0,
      "text": "So now it&#39;s going from fish and sharks into reptiles,"
    },
    {
      "index": 205,
      "start_time": 624128.0,
      "end_time": 627412.0,
      "text": "which, again, this is only one month old,"
    },
    {
      "index": 206,
      "start_time": 627436.0,
      "end_time": 629814.0,
      "text": "but it shows us that we know almost nothing"
    },
    {
      "index": 207,
      "start_time": 629838.0,
      "end_time": 632112.0,
      "text": "about this hawksbill turtle&#39;s vision."
    },
    {
      "index": 208,
      "start_time": 632136.0,
      "end_time": 634992.0,
      "text": "And it makes me think about how much more there is to learn."
    },
    {
      "index": 209,
      "start_time": 635160.0,
      "end_time": 636548.0,
      "text": "And here in the Solomon Islands,"
    },
    {
      "index": 210,
      "start_time": 636572.0,
      "end_time": 640143.0,
      "text": "there&#39;s only a few thousand breeding females of this species left,"
    },
    {
      "index": 211,
      "start_time": 640167.0,
      "end_time": 642211.0,
      "text": "and this is one of the hotspots for them."
    },
    {
      "index": 212,
      "start_time": 642235.0,
      "end_time": 645302.0,
      "text": "So it shows us how much we need to really protect these animals"
    },
    {
      "index": 213,
      "start_time": 645326.0,
      "end_time": 647682.0,
      "text": "while they&#39;re still here, and understand them."
    },
    {
      "index": 214,
      "start_time": 647706.0,
      "end_time": 649850.0,
      "text": "In thinking about biofluorescence,"
    },
    {
      "index": 215,
      "start_time": 649874.0,
      "end_time": 651819.0,
      "text": "I wanted to know, how deep does it go?"
    },
    {
      "index": 216,
      "start_time": 651843.0,
      "end_time": 654286.0,
      "text": "Does this go all the way to the bottom of the ocean?"
    },
    {
      "index": 217,
      "start_time": 654311.0,
      "end_time": 657858.0,
      "text": "So we started using submarines, and we equipped them"
    },
    {
      "index": 218,
      "start_time": 657882.0,
      "end_time": 660550.0,
      "text": "with special blue lights on the front here."
    },
    {
      "index": 219,
      "start_time": 660800.0,
      "end_time": 662400.0,
      "text": "And we dropped down,"
    },
    {
      "index": 220,
      "start_time": 662640.0,
      "end_time": 664781.0,
      "text": "and we noticed one important thing --"
    },
    {
      "index": 221,
      "start_time": 664805.0,
      "end_time": 668103.0,
      "text": "that as we get down to 1,000 meters,"
    },
    {
      "index": 222,
      "start_time": 668127.0,
      "end_time": 669443.0,
      "text": "it drops off."
    },
    {
      "index": 223,
      "start_time": 669467.0,
      "end_time": 673371.0,
      "text": "There&#39;s no biofluorescent marine life down there, below 1,000 meters --"
    },
    {
      "index": 224,
      "start_time": 673395.0,
      "end_time": 675400.0,
      "text": "almost nothing, it&#39;s just darkness."
    },
    {
      "index": 225,
      "start_time": 675424.0,
      "end_time": 677853.0,
      "text": "So it&#39;s mainly a shallow phenomenon."
    },
    {
      "index": 226,
      "start_time": 677878.0,
      "end_time": 679331.0,
      "text": "And below 1,000 meters,"
    },
    {
      "index": 227,
      "start_time": 679355.0,
      "end_time": 682160.0,
      "text": "we encountered the bioluminescent zone,"
    },
    {
      "index": 228,
      "start_time": 682400.0,
      "end_time": 685377.0,
      "text": "where nine out of 10 animals are actually making their own lights"
    },
    {
      "index": 229,
      "start_time": 685401.0,
      "end_time": 687155.0,
      "text": "and flashing and blinking."
    },
    {
      "index": 230,
      "start_time": 687179.0,
      "end_time": 688552.0,
      "text": "As I try to get deeper,"
    },
    {
      "index": 231,
      "start_time": 688576.0,
      "end_time": 691551.0,
      "text": "this is slapping on a one-person submarine suit --"
    },
    {
      "index": 232,
      "start_time": 691575.0,
      "end_time": 695338.0,
      "text": "some people call this my \"Jacques Cousteau meets Woody Allen\" moment."
    },
    {
      "index": 233,
      "start_time": 695362.0,
      "end_time": 696512.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 234,
      "start_time": 696537.0,
      "end_time": 698588.0,
      "text": "But as we explore down here,"
    },
    {
      "index": 235,
      "start_time": 698612.0,
      "end_time": 702331.0,
      "text": "I was thinking about: How do we interact with life delicately?"
    },
    {
      "index": 236,
      "start_time": 702355.0,
      "end_time": 705520.0,
      "text": "Because we&#39;re entering a new age of exploration,"
    },
    {
      "index": 237,
      "start_time": 705760.0,
      "end_time": 706879.0,
      "text": "where we have to take great care,"
    },
    {
      "index": 238,
      "start_time": 706903.0,
      "end_time": 709598.0,
      "text": "and we have to set examples how we explore."
    },
    {
      "index": 239,
      "start_time": 709622.0,
      "end_time": 713286.0,
      "text": "So I&#39;ve teamed up with roboticist Rob Wood at Harvard University,"
    },
    {
      "index": 240,
      "start_time": 713310.0,
      "end_time": 717449.0,
      "text": "and we&#39;ve been designing squishy underwater robot fingers,"
    },
    {
      "index": 241,
      "start_time": 718360.0,
      "end_time": 721462.0,
      "text": "so we can delicately interact with the marine life down there."
    },
    {
      "index": 242,
      "start_time": 721486.0,
      "end_time": 726201.0,
      "text": "The idea is that most of our technologies to explore the deep ocean"
    },
    {
      "index": 243,
      "start_time": 726225.0,
      "end_time": 729500.0,
      "text": "come from oil and gas and military,"
    },
    {
      "index": 244,
      "start_time": 729290.0,
      "end_time": 731870.0,
      "text": "who, you know, they&#39;re not really caring to be gentle."
    },
    {
      "index": 245,
      "start_time": 731894.0,
      "end_time": 734577.0,
      "text": "Some corals could be 1,000 years old."
    },
    {
      "index": 246,
      "start_time": 734601.0,
      "end_time": 737710.0,
      "text": "You don&#39;t want to just go and crush them with a big claw."
    },
    {
      "index": 247,
      "start_time": 737734.0,
      "end_time": 739732.0,
      "text": "So my dream is something like this."
    },
    {
      "index": 248,
      "start_time": 739756.0,
      "end_time": 742520.0,
      "text": "At night, I&#39;m in a submarine,"
    },
    {
      "index": 249,
      "start_time": 742760.0,
      "end_time": 744186.0,
      "text": "I have force-feedback gloves,"
    },
    {
      "index": 250,
      "start_time": 744210.0,
      "end_time": 747528.0,
      "text": "and I could delicately set up a lab in the front of my submarine,"
    },
    {
      "index": 251,
      "start_time": 747552.0,
      "end_time": 750910.0,
      "text": "where the squishy robot fingers"
    },
    {
      "index": 252,
      "start_time": 750115.0,
      "end_time": 752600.0,
      "text": "are delicately collecting and putting things in jars,"
    },
    {
      "index": 253,
      "start_time": 752624.0,
      "end_time": 754209.0,
      "text": "and we can conduct our research."
    },
    {
      "index": 254,
      "start_time": 754607.0,
      "end_time": 757457.0,
      "text": "Back to the powerful applied applications."
    },
    {
      "index": 255,
      "start_time": 757481.0,
      "end_time": 760321.0,
      "text": "Here, you&#39;re looking at a living brain"
    },
    {
      "index": 256,
      "start_time": 760345.0,
      "end_time": 763712.0,
      "text": "that&#39;s using the DNA of fluorescent marine creatures,"
    },
    {
      "index": 257,
      "start_time": 763736.0,
      "end_time": 765742.0,
      "text": "this one from jellyfish and corals,"
    },
    {
      "index": 258,
      "start_time": 765766.0,
      "end_time": 769235.0,
      "text": "to illuminate the living brain and see its connections."
    },
    {
      "index": 259,
      "start_time": 769259.0,
      "end_time": 770775.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s funny that we&#39;re using RGB"
    },
    {
      "index": 260,
      "start_time": 770799.0,
      "end_time": 773347.0,
      "text": "just to kind of satisfy our own human intuition,"
    },
    {
      "index": 261,
      "start_time": 773371.0,
      "end_time": 775704.0,
      "text": "so we can see our brains better."
    },
    {
      "index": 262,
      "start_time": 775729.0,
      "end_time": 777777.0,
      "text": "And even more mind-blowing,"
    },
    {
      "index": 263,
      "start_time": 777801.0,
      "end_time": 780911.0,
      "text": "is my close colleague Vincent Pieribone at Yale,"
    },
    {
      "index": 264,
      "start_time": 780935.0,
      "end_time": 784311.0,
      "text": "who has actually designed and engineered a fluorescent protein"
    },
    {
      "index": 265,
      "start_time": 784336.0,
      "end_time": 786431.0,
      "text": "that responds to voltage."
    },
    {
      "index": 266,
      "start_time": 786455.0,
      "end_time": 789557.0,
      "text": "So he could see when a single neuron fires."
    },
    {
      "index": 267,
      "start_time": 789581.0,
      "end_time": 794120.0,
      "text": "You&#39;re essentially looking at a portal into consciousness"
    },
    {
      "index": 268,
      "start_time": 794144.0,
      "end_time": 797580.0,
      "text": "that was designed by marine creatures."
    },
    {
      "index": 269,
      "start_time": 798102.0,
      "end_time": 802788.0,
      "text": "So this brings me all back to perspective and relationship."
    },
    {
      "index": 270,
      "start_time": 802812.0,
      "end_time": 805510.0,
      "text": "From deep space,"
    },
    {
      "index": 271,
      "start_time": 805750.0,
      "end_time": 808227.0,
      "text": "our universe looks like a human brain cell,"
    },
    {
      "index": 272,
      "start_time": 808251.0,
      "end_time": 810733.0,
      "text": "and then here we are in the deep ocean,"
    },
    {
      "index": 273,
      "start_time": 810757.0,
      "end_time": 813627.0,
      "text": "and we&#39;re finding marine creatures and cells"
    },
    {
      "index": 274,
      "start_time": 813652.0,
      "end_time": 815931.0,
      "text": "that can illuminate the human mind."
    },
    {
      "index": 275,
      "start_time": 815955.0,
      "end_time": 819730.0,
      "text": "And it&#39;s my hope that with illuminated minds,"
    },
    {
      "index": 276,
      "start_time": 819970.0,
      "end_time": 822882.0,
      "text": "we could ponder the overarching interconnectedness of all life,"
    },
    {
      "index": 277,
      "start_time": 822906.0,
      "end_time": 825263.0,
      "text": "and fathom how much more lies in store"
    },
    {
      "index": 278,
      "start_time": 825288.0,
      "end_time": 827300.0,
      "text": "if we keep our oceans healthy."
    },
    {
      "index": 279,
      "start_time": 827270.0,
      "end_time": 828185.0,
      "text": "Thank you."
    },
    {
      "index": 280,
      "start_time": 828209.0,
      "end_time": 833324.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    }
  ]
}